T1  - Deadly Embrace: Sovereign and Financial Balance Sheets Doom Loops
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdx059
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 85
IS  - 3
SP  - 1781
EP  - 1823
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The recent unravelling of the Eurozone’s financial integration raised concerns about feedback loops between sovereign and banking insolvency. This article provides a theory of the feedback loop that allows for both domestic bailouts of the banking system and sovereign debt forgiveness by international creditors or solidarity by other countries. Our theory has important implications for the re-nationalization of sovereign debt, macroprudential regulation, and the rationale for banking unions.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdx059
